Singer Daniel Benson formerly known as Buju has officially switched his professional/stage name to “BNXN” (pronounced simply as Benson). The fast-rising afro-fusion musician made this known on his official Twitter page. He explained the name change became necessary after he was mistaken for another Jamaican singer known as Buju Banton.   Akintoye cancels 87th birthday celebration for Sunday Igboho     Gunmen launch second attack on Okomu oil palm in 72 hours     APC Convention: Between the caretaker and the undertaker   “It’s no longer ‘Buju’. Call me ‘Benson’ written as ‘BNXN’,” the announcement reads. This alteration will take effect immediately from the 18th of February 2022. - Advertisement - A statement by his management said: “It should be appreciated by the general public that Daniel Benson shall now be addressed professionally as “BNXN” concerning all future formal and business correspondence. “Other than the formal change of his professional/stage name, all other details, structures, as well as previous or current contracts and other agreements remain intact and unaltered”. SPONSORED